metadata.title: Groundfish Stomach Contents - U.S. Waters

creators.name: Atmospheric Administration (NOAA), National Marine Fisheries Service (NMFS), Alaska Fisheries Science Center (AFSC)

metadata.description:
Measurement Details
Taxonomic identification, weights, and counts of prey in Groundfish stomach contents.  Emphasis on identification of commercially important prey to species level when possible.  Prey weight measured to nearest milligram.

Geographic Area
Shelf and slope regions of the eastern Bering Sea, Gulf of Alaska, Aleutian Islands, and Washington Oregon California areas.

Publication
Numerous publications available on request from the contact person

Other Comments
sporadic collections (mostly in the summer)


A TCODE project
